         <head type="date">
            <date>January 28, 1805</date>
         </head>
         <div type="entry">
            <sp who="wc">
               <speaker>Clark</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date>28th <hi rend="italic">January Monday</hi> 1805</date>
               </ab>
               <p>
attempt to cut through the ice &amp;c get our Boat and Canoo out without Suckcess, Several Indians here wishing to get war hatchets made [<hi rend="italic">here a drawing</hi>] this shape<ref target="n09012801" n="1"/>    the man Sick yesterday is getting well    <name type="person" key="Jusseaume, René">Mr. Jessome</name> our interpeter was taken verry unwell this evening    warm day
</p>
               <p>
                  <figure rend="aps">
                     <p>War Hatchet, January 28, 1805, Codex C, p. 158
<bibl>
                           <orgName>(American Philosophical Society library, </orgName>
                           <note place="inline"> used with permission.)</note>
                        </bibl>
                     </p>
                  </figure>
               </p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div type="entry">
            <sp who="ml">
               <speaker>Lewis</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date>
                     <hi rend="italic">Monday January 28th 1805</hi>
                     <ref target="n09012802" n="2"/>
                  </date>
               </ab>
               <p>
Observed Equal altitudes with Sextant and artifical Horizon on the construction recommended by <name type="person" key="Ellicott, Andrew">Mr. Andrew Ellicott</name>, in which sperits were substituted for water, it being to could to use the latter.</p>
